abstract: Yesterday's business upon the Stock Exchange affords as strong a contrast to Monday's as could be desired. Upon Monday two casual advances were the exceptions to the general decline. Yesterday two fractional declines were the exceptions to the general advance. The tone, too, was as distinctly good yesterday as it was pessimistic on Monday, and, naturally, whereas prices fell upon the brisker moments on Monday, they advanced yesterday.

Gould brought to Albany to-day a rapid transit bill which is intended to take the place of all of the rapid transit bills now pending, and which, according to Mr. Gould's statement, has the approval of Mayor Low and the city authorities. He gave the measure to Senator Elsberg, and Mr. Elsberg intends to introduce it in the morning.

abstract: WASHINGTON, April 3. -- Charming weather and a card that gave promise of excellent sport attracted the banner crowd of the meeting thus far to the races at Bennings to-day. The track was in fine condition, although a trifle lumpy. The going was altogether the best of the meeting. It was a bad day for the talent, not a single favorite winning, and five out of the six favorites being unplaced.

abstract: GREENWICH, Conn., April 5 -- A freak racing boat, and a novelty in this country, is to be used on Long Island Sound during the coming season. abstract: DALLAS, Texas, April 12. -- It was learned to-night that much friction developed in the meeting of the Texas World's Fair Commissioners held in this city Friday last. Keating of Dallas resigned.

abstract: PARIS, April 18. -- Mrs. F. Moulton was at home last Sunday to a few friends at her pretty apartment in the Champs Elysees. abstract: BERLIN, April 20 -- The thirty-six hours' snowstorm over Middle Europe ceased today at daybreak. The snow is two inches deep in Berlin, increasing to a yard deep in the Hartz highlands and elsewhere. Snow lies deep in East Prussia and Poland. The temperature in most parts of Germany is barely at freezing point, so that the damage to the fruit crops may not be so serious as at first supposed.

abstract: The most important event in the money market is the reappearance here of Wall Street as a very urgent borrower. American bankers effected large borrowings hero last Summer, and again in December; but since the beginning of the year nothing had been heard of such operations till last week. The recent change in the American money market, however, has created a very large demand for money here from New York bankers.

abstract: A correspondent is curious as to why "The Starbucks" was lately called a dramatization of the bookworm disease. As it was written, the word was not "book," but "hook." It was the proofreader who made it "book." abstract: VANCOUVER, B.C., April 29. -- Probably ninety-five persons are dead as a result of a mysterious explosion which tore off the top of Turtle Mountain, overlooking the little town of Frank, in the Province of Alberta, early this morning.
